===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally {{zh-l|*歬}}, an {{Han compound|止|t1=foot|舟|t2=boat|ls=ic|nocap=y}} – a foot on a boat moving forward.

In the current form, {{zh-l|*止}} is simplified to {{zh-l|*䒑}} and {{zh-l|*舟}} to {{zh-l|*月}}. The current form with an additional {{zh-l|*刀|knife}} ([[𠝣]] > [[𣦃]] > 前) is the original form of {{och-l|剪|to cut}}.

Unrelated to [[俞]].

